cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.PL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new logic for characterising probabilistic alternating simulation.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as probabilistic game structures are often used in AI applications such as decision making and planning.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with game structures and simulation relations.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper proposes a new logic for expressing properties in probabilistic game structures.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the behaviour of concurrent games, which can be modelled using data structures and algorithms.
